shed or what lies ahead. The concluding chapter is a comparative study of the role of humane internationalism in the policies of these four countries and a prognosis of the influence which a humane middle-power internationalism may yet have on Northern responses to the challenge of global poverty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Economic Development.2bisacsh1 aCooper, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHveem, Helge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPratt, Cranford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPratt, Cranford, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSödersten, Obo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerloren Van Themaat, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757986940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487579869423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487579869.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK